            <title>[JCR-583] TCK: NodeReadMethodsTest.testGetName fails with NPE if  &apos;testroot&apos; has no child node</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/JCR-583</link>
                <project id="10591" key="JCR">Jackrabbit Content Repository</project>
                        <description>The &amp;#39;testGetName&amp;#39; does not assert, that  the childnode field has been populated during setup.&lt;br/&gt;
if  for whatever reason  the test data don&amp;#39;t provide a single childnode below the test root, this test will fail with nullpointer&lt;br/&gt;
exception.&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
i would like to suggest to use the same assertion as in testGetPath and throw a NotExecutableException in case of&lt;br/&gt;
missing child node.&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
patch attached.&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
</description>
